# Challenge
I stopped using YellowPages and moved onto WhitePages... but the page they gave me is all blank!

# Solution
We start by examining the file by simply printing it. We can see that there are 4 different hex values: `\x20`, `\xe2`, `\x80` and `\x83`. We know that `\x20` is just a regular space and we can see that the 3 others always appear in the same order - `\xe2\x80\x83`. We google `\xe2\x80\x83` and find it's the utf-8 value of `EM SPACE`, so we can consider the three hex values as one character. Thus we have 2 different types of spaces. A normal space and EM space. If we replace the EM space with `0` and the regular space with `1`, we get:
```

```
If we convert those bits to ascii (using `unbits` in `pwn` or any online tool), we get:
```

        picoCTF

        SEE PUBLIC RECORDS & BACKGROUND REPORT
        5000 Forbes Ave, Pittsburgh, PA 15213
        picoCTF{not_all_spaces_are_created_equal_f006c045f6b402ce4bc749dc7a262380}
```

Flag: `picoCTF{not_all_spaces_are_created_equal_f006c045f6b402ce4bc749dc7a262380}`
